  <!-- EN: charm paper -->
  <RI_Resource_CharmPaper.label>符纸</RI_Resource_CharmPaper.label>
  <!-- EN: Ordinary paper used for writing charms. By itself, charm paper has no supernatural power.Once a charm is written on it, however, it becomes a medium for communicating with heaven and earth.\n\nCharm paper is easy to produce, inexpensive, and can be purchased in large quantities from Daoist sects. -->
  <RI_Resource_CharmPaper.description>一种特制的纸，供人写符之用。符纸本身并无神异，但画符后，便可成为沟通天地、镇鬼诛邪的媒介。\n\n这种符纸制作不难，并且价格便宜，能在道门市场大量购买。</RI_Resource_CharmPaper.description>
  
  <!-- EN: concentrated aberrant blood -->
  <RI_Resource_ConcentrateAberrantBlood.label>浓缩邪血</RI_Resource_ConcentrateAberrantBlood.label>
  <!-- EN: A small amount of refined blood extracted from aberrant entities. It is dark red, thick in texture, and radiates an ominous presence.\n\nScholars have found that this blood can resist natural decay, allowing corpses to remain active for long periods. Since aberrant entities began to spread, alchemists, folklorists, and wandering occult practitioners have all sought after it—whether for forbidden rituals, crafting cursed artifacts, or even attempting to reanimate the dead. -->
  <RI_Resource_ConcentrateAberrantBlood.description>从具备肉身的邪祟体内提取的血液，色泽深红，质地浓稠，弥漫着不祥之气。\n\n学者们发现，这种血液能够抵御自然腐败，使尸骸长期保持活性。自邪祟横行以来，炼金术士、民俗学者，以及各类江湖术士皆为此物趋之若鹜——或用于禁忌的仪式，或锻造邪异的法宝，甚至妄图以此令尸体复生。</RI_Resource_ConcentrateAberrantBlood.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Yin oil -->
  <RI_Resource_CorpseOil.label>阴脂</RI_Resource_CorpseOil.label>
  <!-- EN: When solid, it is called fat; when melted, it is called oil.\n\nYin oil is refined from biological corpses. Unlike ordinary oils, it does not easily spoil, which is why candles made from it are known as everlasting lamps. The flame of yin oil burns with a dim green light, and the principle behind it remains unknown. -->
  <RI_Resource_CorpseOil.description>凝者曰脂，释者曰膏。\n\n阴脂是以邪术秘法从尸体中分离获得。它并不像寻常油脂那样容易酸败，所以用阴脂做的蜡烛也被称为长明灯。\n\n点燃阴脂的火光呈幽绿色，温度不高，但其灼烧额外疼痛，其原理至今未知。</RI_Resource_CorpseOil.description>
  
