  <!-- EN: erosion bronze -->
  <RI_Resource_ErosionBronze.label>风磨铜</RI_Resource_ErosionBronze.label>
  <!-- EN: Erosion bronze is a special copper alloy. Its exact smelting formula has been lost, and today it can only be obtained by excavating ancient artifacts made from it deep underground.\n\nLegends say that ancient craftsmen mixed specific minerals into the alloy, giving it unique chemical properties that suppress aberrant entities.\n\nIn modern times, these bronze artifacts are often purchased and reforged into ritual tools and talismans. -->
  <RI_Resource_ErosionBronze.description>风磨铜是一种古代冶炼的特殊铜合金，如今配方已失传，只能从地层中少量挖掘得到。\n\n相传古人在炼制过程中，会混入特定矿石，使其具备独特的化学特性，对邪祟之物有克制作用。古人虽然不知原理，但也会将风磨铜用于铸造铜币和护身符。\n\n到了现代，这些发掘的铜制文物，通常会被人买下，重新打造为法器。</RI_Resource_ErosionBronze.description>
  
  <!-- EN: ink jade -->
  <RI_Resource_InkJade.label>墨玉</RI_Resource_InkJade.label>
  <!-- EN: Ink jade is a deep green jade with a smooth and warm texture, usually found buried underground.\n\nIt has fine patterns and a calm, heavy color, and gives off a faint cold aura. Ancient people believed that wearing ink jade could ward off impurity, calm the mind, and resist misfortune. Some scholars speculate that it contains a weak form of energy that can resonate with the human body. -->
  <RI_Resource_InkJade.description>墨玉是一种质地温润的深绿色玉石，通常在地下被挖掘发现。\n\n墨玉纹理细腻，色泽沉稳，散发出若有若无的清冷气息。古人相信佩戴此物，可辟秽安神，抵御不祥。更有学者推测，其内部蕴含某种微弱的能量，似乎能与人体产生共鸣。因而在诸多典籍中被赋予神秘色彩，常作为祭祀的重要器具。</RI_Resource_InkJade.description>
  
